      {
        "title": "Properly fast, a must for gaming and creating",
        "text": "RAM is perhaps the best \"bang for your buck\" upgrade a computer can receive, as too little memory will act as a bottleneck for even the strongest CPU (even more so if it has an integrated GPU, as that uses RAM for the graphics buffer as well). And a very solid 32Gb set like this does the job beautifully well. Two 16Gb sticks (as they're technically faster than a single 32Gb one), rated to a high read/write speed (which your PC will slow down to its own maximum speed, so no worries about speed compatibility issues), with a clean and aesthetically pleasing heat sink design (the \"Crucial\" name is printed on the thin side, which is a nice touch if you have a glass panel on your PC tower).\n\nAll for a great price, from a veteran name brand, can't beat it. RAM is one component that can genuinely make a computer run \"like new\" (if yours only has ≤8Gb to begin with), as it lets the CPU run to its actual potential. And this kit absolutely delivers.",
