        "title": "Took a few tries but we got it",
        "text": "At first my system wouldn't boot up (HP Z240 Tower Workstation) and I had to reseat the memory several times. I took a deep breath, and deliberately put in the old memory - the system finally boot up. I then powered down and reinstalled the new memory (32GB kit [2x16GB] DDR3-3200 DIMM) and that magic sound of the bios recognizing the new memory chimed in! My system does feel faster - I wish I was running a more leaner OS like a Linux distro (currently I'm using Windows 10 - Build 19045) and I have a LOT of stuff installed.\n\nNot",
